150 grams Jasmine Rice
1 unit(s) Bell Pepper
240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Sugar Snap Peas
1 sachet(s) Thai Style Spice Mix
50 grams Ketjap Manis
15 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
30 milliliter(s) Rice Vinegar
5 grams Roasted White Sesame Seeds
1 tsp Sugar
2 tbsp Tomato Ketchup

Boil a half-full kettle.
Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.
Meanwhile, chop the pepper into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat. Once hot, fry the beef mince, pepper, sugar snap peas and Thai style spice (add less if you'd prefer things milder), 5-6 mins.
Break up the beef as it cooks, then drain the fat.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the ketjap manis, rice vinegar, soy, sugar, ketchup (see pantry for both) and a splash of water.
Simmer, 1 min. Remove from the heat.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the rice between your bowls.
Spoon over the sweet and sticky beef.
Sprinkle over the sesame seeds.
Enjoy!